Thank you for updating this!

Should this be `>=` or `>`? If no IDs have been generated yet, then the `count` is `0`, and calling `getId(0)` ought to fail, so, I think this should just be `>`, right?

Also, you don't need the first assert in this function anymore, it's redundant. It's also an assert rather than a usage error, so it should be updated anyway. I would just do a single check like:

```ts
if (offset >= 0 && offset < this.count) {
	return ...
} else {
	throw new UsageError("Local ID offset out of bounds");
}
```

